{
  "texts": [
    "The dataset they used is from Cohen et al. [14].",
    "The train-test split was 80-20.",
    "The model achieved sensitivity, specificity, precision, accuracy and f1-score of 0.93, 0.97, 0.97, 0.96 and 0.96 respectively for binary classification.Oyelade et al. designed CovFrameNet [21].",
    "The dataset is acquired from 5 sources.",
    "These databases are the \"COVID-19 X-Ray images\" [22], the \"National Institutes of Health (NIH) Chest X-Ray Dataset\" [14], \"COVID-19 Radiography database\" [16], \"COVIDNet\" [11], \"COVID-19 Chest X-Ray\" [23], and \"Actualmed COVID-19 Chest X-Ray Dataset\" (https:// github."
  ]
}